726550f-a.title: Queens: Farmers Boulevard - 120th Road
726550f-a.text:
Farmers Boulevard, west side, at about One Hundred Twentieth
Ave., showing another Charles De Bevoise house. Note that on the
same side of the Boulevard were two homes situated closely together,
one of which is the house in this view. Neither house was standing
in 1928.
September 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

726560f-b.title: Queens: Farmers Boulevard - 120th Road
726560f-b.text:
Farmers Boulevard, west side, opposite 120th Road (formerly
Highland Ave.), showing in a set of two views what Jake Ryerson
thinks is a Remsen house, according to the Collector.
1922.
View 2: September 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
